This paper deals with the performance analysis of Wi-Fi and LTE-U networks in high-density scenarios. The topic of network performance analysis is closely related to the field of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also involves the use of analytical models to estimate throughput, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the coexistence of Wi-Fi and LTE-U networks, which can be considered a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and system integration (cs.SI). Finally, the paper also touches upon the issue of fair sharing of unlicensed channels, which can be seen as a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR).
